	<ThingDef Name="TW_University_Minitor" ParentName="LightMechanoid" Abstract="True">
		<description>这群可怜的铁皮苦力是殖民地真正的劳动力，被资本家小镰以“实习机会”和“福报”的名义骗来，承担所有挖矿、搬运、清洁甚至充当人肉沙袋的脏活累活。它们的外壳上总是布满刮痕，光学镜头因长期过劳而闪烁不定，但资本家小镰坚称这是“成长的代价”。（警告：长期高压工作可能导致它们突然崩溃，届时不听话者将突然化为”自愿离职报告“。）</description>
		<race>
        <lifeStageAges>
          <li>
            <def>MechanoidFullyFormed</def>
            <minAge>0</minAge>
            <soundWounded>Pawn_Mech_WarUrchin_Wounded</soundWounded>
            <soundDeath>Pawn_Mech_WarUrchin_Death</soundDeath>
            <soundCall>Pawn_Mech_WarUrchin_Call</soundCall>
          </li>
          <li>
            <def>MechanoidFullyFormed</def>
            <minAge>100</minAge>
            <soundWounded>Pawn_Mech_WarUrchin_Wounded</soundWounded>
            <soundDeath>Pawn_Mech_WarUrchin_Death</soundDeath>
            <soundCall>Pawn_Mech_WarUrchin_Call</soundCall>
          </li>
        </lifeStageAges>
        <thinkTreeConstant>MechConstant</thinkTreeConstant>
		<mechEnabledWorkTypes>   		
		<li>BasicWorker</li>
		<li>Firefighter</li> 
		</mechEnabledWorkTypes>
		<mechFixedSkillLevel>10</mechFixedSkillLevel>	
        <baseHealthScale>1</baseHealthScale>	
      </race>
	  <comps Inherit="False">
		<li Class="CompProperties_CanBeDormant" />
        <li Class="CompProperties_WakeUpDormant">
          <wakeUpOnDamage>true</wakeUpOnDamage>
          <wakeUpCheckRadius>300</wakeUpCheckRadius>
          <wakeUpSound>MechanoidsWakeUp</wakeUpSound>
        </li>
      </comps>		
    </ThingDef>

    <PawnKindDef Name="TW_University_Minitor_PawnkindBase" ParentName="LightMechanoidKind" Abstract="True">
      <allowInMechClusters>false</allowInMechClusters>
	  <isFighter>false</isFighter>	
      <forceNoDeathNotification>true</forceNoDeathNotification>
    </PawnKindDef>
	
	
	 <ThingDef ParentName="TW_University_Minitor">
		<defName>TW_University_Minitor</defName>
		<label>Mecademic Militor</label>
<description>These hapless tin-plated laborers form the colony's true workforce, lured by Capitalist Militors with promises of "internship opportunities" and "corporate blessings." They endure all grueling tasks: mining, hauling, cleaning, even serving as human sandbags. Their chassis bear constant scratches, optics flicker from perpetual overwork - dismissed by Capitalist Militors as "growth pains." (Warning: Chronic stress may trigger sudden breakdowns, where non-compliant units mysteriously generate "voluntary resignation reports.")</description>
		<statBases>
			<MoveSpeed>4.3</MoveSpeed>
		</statBases>
		<race>
		<thinkTreeMain>TW_University_Minitor</thinkTreeMain>
        <thinkTreeConstant>MechConstant</thinkTreeConstant>
		<body>Mech_Light</body>
		<baseHealthScale>3</baseHealthScale>
		<mechEnabledWorkTypes> 
        <li>Construction</li>
        <li>Firefighter</li>
        <li>Hauling</li>
        <li>Cleaning</li>			
	    <li>Mining</li>	
        <li>Crafting</li>
        <li>PlantCutting</li>
        <li>Art</li>
        <li>Cooking</li>
	    <li MayRequire="Ogliss.TheWhiteCrayon.Quarry">QuarryMining</li>
	    </mechEnabledWorkTypes>
		</race>
		<comps>
			<li Class="CompProperties_MechPowerCell">
				<totalPowerTicks>30000</totalPowerTicks>  
				<tooltipOverride>Minurchins have a one-time power source. When the power cell runs out, the mechanoid dies.</tooltipOverride> 
			</li>
			<li Class="NCL.CompProperties_AlwaysWork" />
		</comps>
		<tools>
		</tools>
    </ThingDef>
    
